now.<br>
<br>
Enough experience with this game to know when to melee, and when to not.  My primary job is to keep everyone alive, and I won't falter from that task.  As long as everyone is on the right page, and knows who to assist, knows their role, etc., I don't think I've ever killed anyone because I was all busy farting around with my hammer's procs.  Possible that I killed Rorack a time or three in my younger days, yeah.... but you know, enchanters are fragile.  I learned to take very good care of them!  They are a top priority for me now.<br>
<br>
But if I have plenty of mana, and nobody is in any immediate danger of death, I will melee, it helps the group.  I put out a fair amount of damage, with the addition of /bash, Yaulp V ( mana regen when it's on, ) and the summoned line of post-50 hammers.  A cleric is fairly decent at causing some abuse, and I can pull in a select few zones, thanks to the upgrade in the Pacify line.  Pulled in SolC last night, nobody died.  But the group's HP bars are my primary concern, and I will drop melee in a second to take care of them.  I hardly ever nuke, because it's an incredible waste of my mana.<br>
<br>
I roleplay, it's why I am on Firiona Vie, but I don't let a group die because I am ignorant of when I should concentrate on being a pure healer.  I learned a lot coming of age on FV from the beginning.  Priest classes that let somebody die because they are having fun meleeing are doing a bad service to the group, and to the community of healers.  Unacceptable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mathyuis>Mathyuis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/22/03 3:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3914.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Battle Cleric/Shaman/Druid</span><hr size=1> 56th season Shaman here<br>
<br>
In my experience, we shaman can solo just fine, however if working with a group and no cleric is available, the healing of the group falls to me.  Now lets see, if no chanter is available, that leaves me doing Haste.  No necro in group, well i'm main DoT too. For planes mobs, I always try to have necro in group, or mage, or someone who can keep DPS up.  My normal groups consist of a warrior, a monk, a cleric, myself, a necro, and another....  <br>
<br>
As far as me meleeing, yeah right......that's why we have pets.  haste the pet, let him deal the damage for you.  Hell at 55 pet quads max damage 60. 9 times out of 10 that's more damage then the shaman can melee out.<br>
<br>
If I get aggro, which as most will tell you, that in my particular case, I gain a lot of aggro :-), then the warrior will normally shield and peel off.  There are weapons out there that can let a shaman deal out exquisite melee damage though, but myself I prefer just to canny, heal, slow, dot, root if necessary, and send in pet.  That's just me, and people will disagree with the way I play, but people seldom die.  I take the lumps in group from gaining aggro, at least gives group more time to kill mob.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp<br>
<br>
Mathyuis De'Akkadian<br>
56th Iksar Shaman<br>
Officer of Indigo Void<br>
