<br>
With yaulp on I can regen mana at a fair clip, so it doesn't hurt to have me swinging the hammer rather than twiddling my thumbs.  That thing procs LOTS, so I can wind up doing 1000dd mana-free on any given mob, which is also noticeably better than twiddling thumbs.<br>
<br>
That's in the best-case scenario, though - where you have a nice high HP tank who holds aggro.  Then you just stop swinging every now and again to cast your complete heal and you're back at it.  If there's an add or aggro is lost, etc - it's not a moment to retarget and cast heals, and I don't believe I have ever let someone fall because I was playing with my big shiny lethal hammer... *drifts into reverie*   <br>
