I think this is mostly a preference thing. Some healing class players like to melee a bit, some don't but it's very possible to melee without really compromising your group's safety at higher levels as long as they are halfway competent.<br>
<br>
The cleric Yaulp line eventually allows them to melee and regenerate mana at the same time so they won't really be losing much in the way of mana from meleeing. With their summoned hammer procs they can contribute noticable damage, especially with haste and pumpkin heads (scarecrow illusion). As already noted though, cleric nukes are horribly inefficient and generally only worth using if there's nothing else to do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Shamen are sort of in a similar situation at higher levels. The later versions of their cannibalize line allow them to regenerate mana quickly so they can afford to screw around a bit if they're not the main healer in a pressure situation.<br>
<br>
If your druid is meleeing then he/she is probably bored :P<br>
